results.name: a(n) = A253565(A003714(n)).
comment: After the initial terms 1, 2 and 3, all other terms can be inductively generated by applying any finite composition-combination of A253560 and A253550 to 3, but with such a restriction that A253560 may not be applied twice in succession.
Note how A253565(A022340(n)) = A253565(2*A003714(n)) yields a permutation of A056911, odd squarefree numbers.
link: Antti Karttunen, Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..10946
xref: Cf. A277334 (same sequence sorted into ascending order).
